12. Generate TLS Certificates
Go to certificate directory:
cd ~/DO280/labs/network-ingress/certs
________________________________________
Step 1 Generate Private Key
openssl genrsa -out training.key 4096
Meaning:
Parameter	Description
genrsa	generate RSA key
4096	key size
training.key	private key file
________________________________________
Step 2 Create Certificate Request
openssl req -new \
-key training.key -out training.csr \
-subj "/C=US/ST=North Carolina/L=Raleigh/O=Red Hat/CN=todo-https.apps.ocp4.example.com"
Purpose:
Create CSR (Certificate Signing Request).
Important field:
CN = hostname
________________________________________
Step 3 Sign Certificate
openssl x509 -req -in training.csr \
-CA training-CA.pem \
-CAkey training-CA.key \
-out training.crt
Purpose:
CA signs certificate.
Files created:
training.key
training.csr
training.crt
________________________________________
13. Create TLS Secret
Command:
oc create secret tls todo-certs \
--cert certs/training.crt \
--key certs/training.key
Explanation:
Option	Meaning
secret tls	TLS secret
--cert	certificate
--key	private key
Secret will be mounted in pod.
________________________________________
14. Deploy TLS Application Version
Deployment file:
todo-app-v2.yaml
New features:
•	HTTPS server
•	port 8443
•	TLS secret mounted
Command:
oc create -f todo-app-v2.yaml
Check mounted volume:
oc set volumes deployment/todo-https
Example:
secret/todo-certs mounted at
/usr/local/etc/ssl/certs
Meaning:
Application can read certificate.
________________________________________
15. Create Passthrough Route
Command:
oc create route passthrough todo-https \
--service todo-https \
--port 8443 \
--hostname todo-https.apps.ocp4.example.com
Architecture now:
Client
  │ HTTPS
  ▼
Router
  │ HTTPS (passthrough)
  ▼
Service
  │ HTTPS
  ▼
Pod
Router does not decrypt traffic.
________________________________________
16. Test TLS Route
Command:
curl -vv -I \
--cacert certs/training-CA.pem \
https://todo-https.apps.ocp4.example.com
Important output:
SSL certificate verify ok
Meaning:
Certificate chain valid
________________________________________
17. Verify Encryption Internally
Get service IP:
oc get svc todo-https -o jsonpath="{.spec.clusterIP}"
________________________________________
Create debug pod:
oc debug -t deployment/todo-https \
--image registry.ocp4.example.com:8443/ubi8/ubi:8.4
________________________________________
Test HTTP:
curl -I http://172.30.121.154
Output:
301 Moved Permanently
Location: https://172.30.121.154:8443
Meaning:
HTTP redirect to HTTPS
________________________________________
Test HTTPS:
curl -k https://172.30.121.154:8443
Result:
HTML output
Application works securely.
